  <discussion>The leaves of var. sionis tend to be narrower and more deeply lobed than those of var. trilobatus; morphologic intermediacy makes these plants hard to separate even at varietal rank. Differences in habitat and an essentially allopatric distribution, however, suggest that two evolutionary entities are present.</discussion>
